Then we can simplify the integration as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\int\mathrm{d}\mathbf{r}\mathbf{E}_{\omega}\left(\mathbf{r}\right)\cdot\boldsymbol{\xi}\left(\mathbf{r}\right) & = & \frac{2\mu_{01}^{2}{\cal R}_{\omega}}{4\pi\epsilon_{0}}\int\mathrm{d}\mathbf{r}^{\prime}\int\mathrm{d}s\mathrm{d}\theta d\phi\times s^{2}\sin\theta e^{iks}\delta^{3}\left(r^{\prime}\right)\delta^{3}\left(s\right)\nonumber \\
 &  & \left[\left({\color{blue}-\frac{ik}{s^{2}}+\frac{2}{s^{3}}}{\color{teal}-\frac{k^{2}}{s}-\frac{ik}{s^{2}}}\right)\cos^{2}\theta-\left({\color{blue}\frac{1}{s^{3}}}{\color{teal}-\frac{ik}{s^{2}}}\right)\sin^{2}\theta+{\color{red}\frac{k^{2}}{s}}\right]
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

Then we carry out the 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 and 
